    "scripture": "and BE renewed in the spirit of your mind,\nEphesians 4:23 \n",
    "content": "Be is a verb that means to exist, to happen, to have a specific state, characteristic or identity. \n\nThe life of a new creation, who has a new heart and a new mind;  our present life is one of being then consequently doing. \n\nWe don't do to be, we be to do, that is the order. \n\nActually it's easier, possible and not burdensome to do things from a place of being than the frustrating legalistic  posture of doing to be. \n\nWe don't tell believers what to do and what not to do without first showing them who they are, and what God did and is doing in them and through them. \n\nWe don't tell believers what to do or what not to do while denying or doubting who God has made them as if it's what they do or don't do that made or makes them who they are in Christ, they are 100% new, new creations without their or our opinion/estimation/contribution. \n\nWhen you study the Epistles in a non legalistic way,  without the veil of Moses and the veil of the old covenant (the Law) and the righteousness of the Pharisees you will realise that every instruction the writers give to the Church starts from first showing the Church (believers) who they now are.  They were not setting letters of rules and regulations but coming from the place of revealing to the believers who they now were and because of getting them to understand and know  who they now were the believers could then do this or that in accordance and consonance with their new nature (Christ). \n \nBut you [are] a chosen generation, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, His own special people, that you may proclaim the praises of Him who called you out of darkness into His marvelous light; who once [were] not a people but [are] now the people of God, who had not obtained mercy but now have obtained mercy.\n1 Peter 2:9-10\n\nIn simple terms it is not what you do or don't do that makes you a new creation, you are already existing as a new creation.  It is  your  new Spirit, new heart and new nature  that should dictate your thoughts, emotions, decisions, choices, words, actions and life through the Holy Spirit in you.  \n\nNew creation is your present state and identity, therefore it is from being you (the new creation you now are) that you think, feel, say and do the things that new creations ought to think, feel, say and do. \n\nSo our theme Scripture is saying - BE RENEWED.  Pointing you and ushering you to an already existing state and process of renewal going on within your mind.  \n\nThe Scripture is not telling you to do the mental work of renewal as if it's not already going on,  as if it's dependant on you, No!  that would be pointing you to vain human efforts, empty dead mental work...to doing what is already being done by God,    \n but the scripture is telling you to be  pointing you to who you already are in MIND, to the renewing work of the Holy Spirit ongoing within you.  \n\nBe always conscious of and yielded to the process of mind renewal by the Holy Spirit, letting it to run its free course in you uninterruptedly.  Let the Holy Spirit continually renovate, refresh, make new again and reform your mind. \n\n Embrace who you now are right from within, identify with your new God given  mind, new soul, new language, new life, new thoughts, new imaginations, new emotions, new meditations, new inner-workings of the Spirit of God.\n\n I WILL give you a new heart and put a new spirit within you; I WILL take the heart of stone out of your flesh and give you a heart of flesh. I WILL put My Spirit within you and cause you to walk in My statutes, and you will keep My judgments and do [them.]\nEzekiel 36:26-27\n",
